I Got accepted for a rental property and was asked to put down a deposit without even seeing the property. I asked to see the property first and arrangements were made. I brought my girlfriend along and we viewed the property. The next day I followed up and they were concerned that my girlfriend did not submit an application. She had no plans to move in but she submitted an app anyway. The following week I received an email saying I was declined. I responded that I had already been approved and that I didn't see any reason that should change. They responded that the denial was based on my co-applicants credit. I explained that she has better credit than I do, as our documents show. Did not hear back. The only explanation I can think of is that my girlfriend is a latin immigrant, and the homeowner-who we met and who screens the applications _did not like this fact. Upset but glad I didn't sign the lease</Review>

I rented with Cornette for almost a total of 5 years. I rented 3 different properties from them. Each time the staff has always been friendly and always eager to help in any way they can.

Ericka has always been so helpful and informational whenever I had issues.

I moved out of my most recent rental house in March and there were some issues in regards to the deposit and some damages within the unit. I emailed Cornette and spoke with Monica, who was very friendly. I shared with her my concerns and she was able to speak with the owner of the property and we were able to come to an agreement on charges.

Ericka, Monica, and the rest of the staff are great and I highly recommend them to anyone who is looking to rent in the Sacramento area.</text>

This management company is awful. Me and my husband applied to 1 house. On their website they have a link you can go to, to see if there are any pending applications. On the one we were applying to there were not any pending applicants. So we applied and paid the fee. They also ask a question on your application if there are any other properties your interested in. There were so we listed them incase our application didn't go through on the first. Btw the other 2 houses we put on our applications also didn't have any pending applications.

They email me back and say the property we applied for had been rented, our second preference didn't allow pets, and our third preferencethey were waiting on a deposit. Confused and irritated because they had misinformation on their website I emailed them. I asked for a refund and told them they needed to update their website.

I got an email back saying they take in 10 applications per listing and let the owner choose (they dont say that on their webaite though) and they won't refund us. The application fees are 40 dollars. They basically rob you of your money. 120 dollars they robbed me and my family during a pandemic.... This management company is a joke. I'd give it no stars if I could. Awful and greedy people.</Text>

<Rating>1< /Rating>< text>
TLDR; Don't waste your time and money on this company.

On 10/6/20 I came across a listing for a studio apartment which would not be available until 11/20/20. By 10/11/20 I had not heard back from Cornette Property Management. There weren't any pictures of the interior but since I knew a previous resident, I was confident I wanted to live at this property and applied through the website. On 10/15/20 I heard back from a "Credit Manager", Sarah, who informed me I'd need a co-signer since I had previously rented from a family member (they just saw the same last name, didn't know who the family member or what the situation was) and had only been at my current job for 4 months. I have been through the probationary period in my role and have even been promoted. They did not ask about the details of this nor about my previous job history. If they had, they'd have learned that I had worked in property management for a National company and am very familiar with the policies and procedures in regards to Fair Housing. When I responded offering more rental references and offered an explanation in employment, it took "Credit Manager", Kaitlyn, four days to let me know my application had gone inactive despite the fact that I had responded to the last email immediately.

The lack of communication and ridiculous policies that are not fluent throughout the industry not only caused me to take a hit on my credit and throw away $40, but realize that the reviews (online and from previous residents at multiple properties I've spoken with) are true and that Cornette Property Management is not a company I will ever rent from or recommend. I'm honestly glad I found out now as opposed to after signing a contract.<//text>

<pictures>None< /pictures>< Text>
As a landlord my experience with Cornette has been excellent in many respects. I have had the displeasure of living through a gamut of issues with my properties and Cornette has always delivered in a professional and timely fashion to help solve those issues. A property management company's job is precisely to alleviate the stress of managing rentals and Cornette delivers in spades with experience and courtesy.

Maintenance issues are dealt with swiftly, with intelligence (and even good humor!) by Monica. She is able to narrow down the problem and call up on just the right amount of professional help to take care of multiple problems economically and in one trip. Monica's vendor selection I found to be excellent and they provide professional work at competitive rates so much so that I don't bother shopping around anymore.

April, the turnover specialist, helped me *completely* renovate a unit that was utterly trashed in just three weeks flat, ahead of schedule AND under budget with change to spare for a few nice upgrades... April even helped me solve some issues by quickly taking the initiative on some decisions with paint and flooring which made my life happy. Thank you!

Jessica was invaluable in navigating the always tricky decisions of rent increase, market pricing and regulation regarding rent increase caps. Jessica is also a great resource for some quick rental market analysis and comps. Emily who works with Jessica helped me track down a tenant who did not make full rent payments and while I dread receiving a late payment notice I am confident they are on top of things always.

Last but not least Elena who was actually my first contact at Cornette I credit with strongly influencing my decision to sign up with Cornette. She has always been very personable with me on the phone and has great insight into what tenants like to see. She takes care of touring properties and has a pulse on the market.

Quite frankly after reading all the angry reviews on here I was highly skeptical of Cornette when I first signed in. Elena helped alleviate some of those issues and then experience showed that sometimes the keyboard warriors are wrong. Oh and did I mention that Cornette management rates are simply unmatched in all of the Sacramento area? (I know I looked at about a dozen alternative!)

Thank you Monica, April, Jessica, Emily and Elena. You guys rock.< /Text>

We are hands on from afar about these details and April and Nancy were always patient with our frequent inquiries about the bids and approach to the work that was being done. They are strict on tenant move-out responsibilities re: cleaning and condition of the property. I would recommend that tenants read leases very carefully about cleaning responsibilities and notify re: anything that they find amiss with the property when they move in . And, take advantage of Cornette's option for tenants to be present at the move out inspection to ensure they have the opportunity to discuss any issues.  As landlords we have sometimes approved Cornette to waive some move out charges if we feel on balance we've had a good tenant, but not every owner will do the same.</review>

I love Gomo's Fish Market. Whenever I‚Äôm hungry and in Inglewood CA, I think of  Gomo‚Äôs Fish Market. Gomo‚Äôs is a take-out restaurant that has the best seafood gumbo in Los Angeles. My wife and children love the fried shrimp lunch special. The coating on the shrimp is amazing. My favorite is the charbroiled filet of Sole in garlic butter sauce. It is served to me on a bed of rice and a side of greens. It‚Äôs very delicious. Steven takes my order, give me an estimated time the food will be ready, and hands my prepared food when it‚Äôs ready. <UserId.>116714505581452635156</UserId.><user_name>Ms toy4xt<//user_name>< date>
1536948270251</date>
< Rating>
5< /Rating>
< review>
This is the best fish on this side of town. The fish is well seasoned without being salty. I don't usually like filet of sole, however, there is something about their filet of sole.  It is delicious. The french fries are good too.  I get them with no salt. I haven't had much luck with the other sides, but I'm very picky. I think my husband said the greens were good there. My husband loves the catfish and orange roughy. They also have sanddabs and they grill fish too. The tartar sauce is made in house and is very good.  If you like tartar, make sure you get extra.  There is an extra charge though.  Don't be put off because it is a hole in the wall kinda place, as most fish markets are.  The kitchen is very clean and they have an A rating.  I almost forgot the jumbo shrimp....mmmmmm good!< /review>

< Review>
I checked into this motel a little after 9pm on a Thursday night. After ringing the front doorbell I was greeted by a nice older gentleman who checked me and my brother in. Upon entering our room with 2 beds we noticed a roach box next to the TV. I used the toilet and when I flushed the chain fell off of the set up inside the toilet tank. I had to stick my hand into the water of the tank and reconnect the chain ao that it would flush again. I then went back into the room and as I was getting ready for sleep I saw a roach on the wall above my head board. After killing it and pulling the sheets back I was able to get some sleep. Not a horrible stay but would've preferred a non smoked in room, no roaches and a working toilet.</Review>

A Monterey Judge said no one can buy anything of mine unless i knew i owned it and approved of the sale.. he ordered everything returned to my dad's estate... He told me to get an attorney but i can not since i have no money and no proof.

the people who are running the place do not really care at times about the guests.

5</rating>
< review>
Wow. Just wow. Incredible service and extremely flavorful broths. My first time here tonight and I wasn't exactly sure what to expect. This place delivered flavor, service, and everything I needed for a chilly evening out.

Our server was all over it. He helped us with sauces, he gave us amazing suggestions, and even put together his personal favorite dipping sauces for us to try.

They end the meal with a bowl of beef, green onions, and/or cilantro so you can scoop the soup into your bowl and enjoy it as a soup! If you're like me and aren't a fan of cilantro, you can enjoy the bits of beef with your broth.

My water cup was never empty because they were always checking on us and making sure everything was refilled. This is amazing in and of itself, because typically these self service food restaurants would drop the food off and you'd never see them again, but our waiter was always there when we needed him.<//review>

2</rating>
<review>We used to visit this place frequently as it is in the heart of a nice Irvine shopping center.
They have plenty of options for meats and seafood and the bar area has many choices of veggies and sauces.
The also offer you a wide selection of soup bases.

The reason why we stopped coming here is because they started charging for things that used to be included in the (already pricier than normal) tap.
The soup bases suddenly required an extra $3 - $6 depending on what you choose.
The salad bar suddenly came with an extra upcharge as if veggies are super expensive.
The portions of the meats started to shrink while raising the prices across the board.

At this point, there are way too many similar and cheaper options available in Orange County.
It was fun while it lasted.</review><pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPxiPgkBy5g4Eeg8IudZMiFD1O9Ft79CdOVed7I=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNqKDNcrVsSBoUduOhHSW9Hsyq3lIby41x5Sava=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMAvQ-F8Uo3knBByf0pTPCsxCwxkobPDd5MriXU=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pics>< Response>

<Text>The service and quality of food is excellent!! I would say Haidilao has number one service for Taiwanese/ Chinese restaurant. Dintaifung is on the second compared to Haidilao. We enjoy having dinner gatherings at this location. The staffs are really attentive. Thank you Robert and Hunter for taking care of our table for a special birthday dinner.

We got filtered spicy, mushroom, tomato and water base. There are other delicious options! The dancing noodles are must get -- comes with a performance and the noodles are so fresh. In two mins you have chewy noodles. I usually like to get frozen tofu, fish ball with egg roe, Napa cabbage, bean curd, fish cake, and Angus beef.

Many sauces to customize to your liking. I usually like the seasame sauce with green onions. The sauce bar also has potato salad, edamame, tomatoes, melon and desserts.

Highighly recommend making reservations beforehand -- it gets busy after 6pm.< /Text><userid>106538710158412913945<//userid></record>

< Review>
Hot pot style cooking.  Lots of choices for broth, meats, veggies.  All you can eat of the little appetizers.  Free kids meal if you want it, with your adult meal.  Spicy options abound.  Make your own sauce for dipping.  The restaurant is large, split into two suites.  The restrooms are well kept and stocked with more than the usual accoutrements.  Good for kids.  Everyone gets an apron.  Even the napkins are nicer than the usual.  The waiting area outside has seats and snacks, as well as complementary drinks.  We even caught the traditional Chinese dancer show in the evening.  The server was great, fast, and thoughtful.<//Review>

Good interactive service. Very strong stock base. It was my first time having hot pot at midnight that I think I shouldn't have. I slept that night and woke up with the same taste in my throat.

<rating>5</rating><text>I love haidilao!

As a semi-vegetarian person, I can confidently say they've great variety in soup bases and plates/dishes. Also having a good spice tolerance, I can also confidently add that the spicy soup base is killer spicy. If you have mid to low tolerance, this is numbing. Flavorful yes, but numbing.

Parking is common to all shops in diamond jamboree and fills up rather quickly. These guys always have a wait list too. So make sure you call in and reserve a spot on the list.

Also yelp check-ins give great deals like free juices.<//text><Pics>None<//Pics><Response>None<//Response>< Gmap_id>

<user_name>Mhar A< /user_name><Time>1536036876466<//Time><rate>5</rate>< review>
Impeccable service! Not your usual Chinese or hot pot restaurant. We opted for the four palace broth ( mushroom,  spicy pork, pork and tomato). We liked them all with the family's as the tomato and mushroom. The Angus and short ribs were a hit. The help yourself sauces were bomb, with of course my favorites are the mushroom and fried chili. There were fruits and Chinese popcorn for patrons waiting with fruit infused water. The milk tea did not disappoint. We thoroughly enjoyed the meal. We came to check it out, we left with full tummies and happy with the experience. The place is also clean and you're provided with house aprons before you eat.<//review>

It was our first time to this location and I have to say, we have been back in the same week since. If you ever meet Michelle, she is one of the sweetest people we‚Äôve met. She was our server and spoiled our little girl with little toys for entertainment. When we came back the second time, she remembered our daughter‚Äôs name. We are regulars to several places in the area and even our usual servers don‚Äôt even remember our names, let alone our daughter‚Äôs.
Michelle, if you ever see this, please know how truly amazing and special you are. Your kindness and thoughtfulness is rare. Your thoughtful towards our nearly one year old will always resonate with us. You‚Äôve set an even higher standard now. Thank you so very much!

The value for the food is great. For those who complain about the price, I‚Äôm not sure how since you see the price of what you order on your IPad... my husband and I are foodies. We are small but we do love to eat and what we order fills us up. Great value for the price and it‚Äôs always been very clean when we arrive. We live 35 minutes away and can‚Äôt wait to come back.

< Review>
It's better to reserve a table at this restaurant, since a lot of people do eat here and there's a long line, but this place actually has complimentary snacks and flavored water outside for the people waiting for a table here.  The staff is friendly here, place looks clean, restrooms has extra amenities that cater to almost every need (i.e. pads, toothpicks, mouthwash, toothbrush, hairspray, etc.).  Food tastes great and the entertainers were cool.  The only downside to this place is how expensive everything is.  Would still return here though.</Review>

<review>I came here first time with my family on my birthday and it was a Friday. Super crowded but we joined live wait list and saved time! When we came, we only waited a little bit more for the table. Since our wait was more than an hour total, they rewarded us on the fortune wheels that got us a free clam dish value around $10. Freebies always make you happy.

I like the interior with colorful, simple set up yet traditional and modern Chinese vibe. The table set up with drawers with hair tie (girls are all appreciated it just like me), wet wipes for phone screens, and napkin. Love the thoughtfulness! We all die for little details. Moreover, the spoons we used were tiny which allow the soup to cool down when it reached your mouth. Another detailed oriented details! Talking about the food, the pot allows us to order 4 soup bases at a time. My favorites are Mushroom and Spicy Pork soup bases. Veggies, seafood and meat options were fresh. The quality is consistent on other times that I come to Hailidao as well. Salad and fruits were provided at the bar with a lot of sauces that you can mix to use with the hot pot.

The best part is their birthday perks. My mom and sister asked the restaurant to prepare and they didn't fail to surprise us. They brought a 'Happy Birthday' sign singing, a fruit dish with candle and a small gift of a spoon and pair of chopsticks. Very cute and fun experience!<//review><resp>None</resp></record></dataset><record>

<user_id>105459183045658723000<//user_id>< review>
No AC. Place gets sweaty when packed. You'll depend on ceiling fans to stay cool, and the wind is concentrated on certain spots on the dance floor. Been here a few times, I do have fun. Last time was on first Friday of the month, when they usually play hip-hop with live DJ. 5 dollar cover charge for those busy weekend days. Can get busy enough that the only single bar can be saturated with patrons so waiting to buy a drink can be 10 minutes. You can play pool, you can dance, you can sit (they have tables)... and you can sweat. I'm sure I'll have fun the next time... albeit with the right people.<//review>

0x80d954f4286370db:0x99a7f5a243e393d1<//gmapID>
< Review>
Bar Pink is the first stop on any self respecting punkers bar crawl the bar is owned by local legend Swami John Reis who you may unremember from such acts as rocket from the crypt, Hot snakes, Drive like jehu, The night marchers, and things his enchanting wife may or may not have called him in anger. Maybe you know him from his radio work or better yet a little show called Yo Gabba Gabba. The Swami is a showman and all around talented devil who features some of the best music you're going to hear in SD. For me, a Bar Pink stop is mandatory before all concerts. A tiki or two, a rousing game of pac man, some good music, good people, goodnight.

*Also bring cash, or the bartenders will try to kill you with their minds.  I think we have time from an evolutionary standpoint before one of them develops telekinesis. Just play it safe.< /Review>

<Rating>5</Rating>< review>
This "dive bar" was an excellent place to meet up with an old punk rockstar to see him perform, Chris Doherty from Gang Green, and to find a GREAT new band, called DethSurf, both who are pictured in my review. (DethSurf's singer and guitarist are pictured with the "kiss" paint on their faces). The clientele were nothing but creative people everywhere, musicians, photographers, artists and rock label entrepreneurs. I was waited on by an excellent bar staff and felt right at home for some reason, as everyone there wanted to buy me a drink. Good to go for great music and killer peeps. Not douchey at all! Thanks San Diego, you never disappoint.<//review>

101888653869131135956</UserId.>
< Name>
Roberto Garcia Ozua</Name>
<Time>1417728345769< /Time>< Rating>
5</Rating>
< Review>
Favorite dive bar in North Park. I discovered this joint back in 2008, and it hasn't change much. Great craft beer selection (and cheap macros if that's your thing, they got $2 tecates and $4 PBR tallboys!) and their specialty cocktails are off the chain - I suggest you try their signature Sneaky Tiki.

If you decide to venture in, check-it out on a Friday or Saturday night. They usually have local bands that get the crowd dancing and howling. On off nights, I find that Monday and Tuesday are usually the best days to find local entertainment.

Since I been going to Bar Pink, I can't think of a night that I have been disappointed. I recommend getting a group of friends together to bar hop to the near by Office Bar or U31 to make it a fun night.<//Review>

< review>
This is both a day use and camping spot.  I‚Äôm unclear of the prices as nothing is posted at the entrance.  The gentleman at the entrance charged us $4 for each adult and $2 dollars for kids older than 5. Nevertheless, it was worth the charge.  Cash only. Pets are welcomed.
The park has picnic tables, porta-potties scattered throughout. Some spots have grills as well.  There is a lot of fishing going on and overall people camping in Rv and tents. Oh, fires are allowed.  Definitely worth checking this place out.< /review>

< name>
CJ Rosendahl</name>
<text>Peaceful, pretty place to camp along a cut-off loop of the San Joaquin River just on the north edge of Fresno. At least it was quiet when I was there mid-week in early October. Grassy, shady areas to camp with picnic tables near the water. Camped 3 nights, only one of those nights were there other people there. Mostly it seems like people go to the other side of this lake, or whatever it is, to fish. Nice respite from cold mountain camping to resupply in Fresno.

The only issue I found was trying to pay. Got there late the 1st night & looked around for some sign about paying or price. There's nothing. No one even came to collect until the 3rd day. I was thinking it was free. It isn't.  Camping cost is $18 per night. Maybe a bit steep for no bathroom just porta-Potty & no water as far as I could tell. But still worth it I think. Still, with no posted camping fee, they could basically charge you whatever they think you could pay.

Bit hard to find. Small handmade sign & it looks like you are driving into someone's yard as you enter area. Not an RV camping place, mostly tent camping.</text><Rating>4< /Rating><userid>117472823435362136534</userid><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNp_5unKtSlkBcfXdiQGTjGd9kGAo0EKjwc3I-S=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMj66ydPXVZO3OduMcpmipy4GbXFcWvI-F0f_1r=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipO3H5Kiz9eTd8HA6ZGxeVkbVEkB81lBIJDWpavP=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNqeQAwGknAsOHIJnQbXQgZmzSrZSRZbsyDxDyM=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pictures>< Date>

<rating>5</rating><text>This place is pretty cool. It's like $4 a person to get in (cash only). But you can bring bbq and beer and whatever else you want, and spend all day here. The back side is against the river, and the front is a little lake. The river is super cold, but it's really fresh and clean water. The lake part is warmer, but the water is kinda murky because of all the sand. It's a really chill place to come and chill with family and friends. Parking and driving through gets a little difficult later in the day with all the cars. There's a port-a-potty in the back at the end of the dirt road, but I recommend leaving and going to the nearest shopping center to use the restroom. Just tell the guy at the gate you're coming back so they dont recharge you. I guess you can also camp here for as long as you want too. There's RVs and tents everywhere.

Overall it's a good getaway spot, not too far, and not too expensive. Perfect for a day trip.< /text><pics>None</pics><response>None<//response><Gmap_id>0x80944275d62328d9:0x9c84d82c45d12923< /Gmap_id></record></dataset><record>

<resp>None<//resp><rate>5< /rate><text>Very comfy location, Beautiful year round campground. So slide to town but feels like you're roughing it in the country. Clean porta-potties, clean campsites with picnic tables and bbq pits.  Trash cans provided at every site. Pitch your canopy or tent, park your camper trailer or RV (Electricity and water hookup available for add'l fee) swimming and tube floating in the private pond with immediate access to the river.  Kayak rental available (call for availability) No showers available so bring your camping shower and tarp, lol!  Fishermen welcome but must be licensed.  Prices are the best around.  Dog friendly... ByoPooper Scooper and bags.  The Beach is open year round unless it is time to trim down trees or deep clean after a busy weekend or holiday. 3 day overnight maximum unless otherwise arranged with the owner.  Owner and Caretaker are on site to assist patrons and there needs also if you forget to bring camp fire wood they do have some for sale.   Bring your family on a little weekend getaway without having to go too far.  I highly recommend this hidden treasure and my family and I will always return.< /text><Gmap_id>0x80944275d62328d9:0x9c84d82c45d12923</Gmap_id><userid>101509225033707363826<//userid><pictures>None</pictures><time>1549319418460</time></record>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
I can not praise Pete and his team enough. Moving to California was a rough enough transition. Finding a home in California in this competitive market... Talk about a headache that him and his team took on for me. They pulled off the impossible.

First let me start, they respected my right to be an Independent Buyer. I was motivated and on a time line. I came with my pre-approval and made it clear I was Independent. They never pressured me to do business with them, they let me do it on my own. They gained my loyalty by being there.

Next, I am a Veteran with a baby on the way. I believe I earned my right to 0 down home loan. VA home loans are not really zero down. You have to pay closing costs. As you know that can get pretty expensive.

Not only that... I am cheap. They managed to help me find and get a home into Escrow for at $0 cost to me. They worked out for the seller to take on all closing costs. And having a baby on the way, we can use all the money we can get.

Pete and his team did a great job. 5 star service all the way.< /review>

< text>
The better half and I decided we needed a new car, but we don't have time to go car shopping because of our work schedules and the kids school schedules. I was about the just give up on a getting one all together because by the time we get a chance to go and look all the good deals are gone. Anyways, long story short, we saw a car we were really interested in online. I click on it send my information to get a price, and I kid you not my phone was ringing within minutes. We fill out a credit application online, being that it was later in the evening we only got offers from a couple banks. So we decided to wait until the next morning to see what other offers were offered. Accepted an offer on my first break at work, and the car was delivered to me all the way in Madera by the time I came home for lunch. If that's not great customer service I don't know what is. If you're looking for a new Chevy, this is the place to buy! Rene Saldivar was great, and I highly recommend that you check them out. Never in a million years did I think I'd buy my first brand new vehicle online, like who does that ??? Well we did and I'm soooo glad we did. I absolutely love my new car.<//text>

<user>116478572491371225996<//user>< Review>
Incredible experience all around!  I've been shopping for quite some time for my new baby.  I've been to dealerships all over Central California, searched online, and made countless calls.

Headed home I passed the Liberty Chevrolet at Selma Auto Mall and decided to call.  I spoke with Rene who selected a few vehicles that fit my search criteria.  He even waited passed closing time for me to get back to the area!

I immediately fell IN LOVE with my new 2018 Chevy Camaro 2ss Redline - it's perfect!

We ran the numbers and carefully considered the vehicle.  After a few HOURS of me going back and forth I told Rene I would be back after consideration (and after bank approvals).  He was patient and totally understanding.

Rene answered all of my questions quickly and honestly.  When he didn't have an answer he was prompt to research and get me the information quickly.  He was overall very knowledgeable about this vehicle and several others I'd inquired about.

My experience with Rene and Selma Auto Mall could not be more incredible.  I'm very impressed with the customer friendly attitudes from all staff, the clean spacious customer environment, and their willingness to do whatever it took to make sure I was completely ecstatic with my purchase.

Thank you Rene, and thank you Selma Auto Mall!</Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
These guys run a family business and they're great!
When Michael, the owner, gives you an estimate, THAT is the price you pay. You'll never hear any excuses about "this here, that there, oh and an other thing about this."
What Michael tells you, he and his son Junior go out of their way to do for you.
If you're vehicle needs an extra part he didn't quote you on, they take care of it, while at the same time jumping through hoops with your insurance company to handle the legal nonsense on your behalf.

A friend of mine had recommended it to me when my girlfriend needed body work done as the lease on her Prius was ending (which they did excellent work on) and now they've done great work for me too.

When I was in the office, I saw an unattended computer open with their Google reviews page open. What that tells me is; this is a business striving to build a reputation on doing good, honest work. And they absolutely do!
If you need work done, this is the place.<//text>

***STAY AWAY FROM THESE DISHONORABLE SHOP!!!!  *****

So I took my car in for a small little repair. I have been going to this shop for years and I know mike through my father. I figured it would be a good place to take my car due to the fact that it's a family owned and they repair high end vehicles, so I felt secure and safe.

This isn't a vehicle I drive on a daily bases, so when I picked up the car I was in a big rush and didn't have a minute to really look at the car closely. However, I have my detailers that come to my home once a week or sometimes twice a week and he notices all the scratches on the car. I asked him what is this from. He stated that this is from the body shop. This is from overspray, and improper care for the vehicle when it was at the shop. So, I asked him how to fix this issue and he told me that it would cost about 850.00 to fix.

Naturally, I was very upset and I drove the car over to the shop and told him to fix it. He decide that he will give me the name of his Detailer and that it would be cheaper. I kept calling the guy and he never responded. He didn't respond to text, calls or anything for that matter.

I called the owner Michael and he started to make excuses and I told him if I cannot get this done immediately, I will have to do it on my own and he will be on the hook for the 850.00. He got very upset with me and told me he would pay for half and I said, I shouldn't be responsible for something his shop made a mistake on and left scratches and overspray on my 200k Porsche.

I have still not received the money I paid and he kept telling me he will pay for half and never got that back either. I had to detail my car several times and still have the damage on my vehicle with no remorse from him!

He thinks the law doesn't apply to him and he thinks that he there is no way to get justice.

I will be taking this guy to court as well!

This is absolutely ridiculous!!< /Review>

<GmapID>0x80946618708b8893:0xe2db84fa5bd33cbe< /GmapID>< Response>
None</Response>
<Text>There has been a big decline in the appeal for going to HomeTown Buffet since all the TV commercials claiming how great the place is began airing.
The greatly reduced menu options are a turn-off. The choices now seem to be very limited.

For us, the very best single menu item, the Orange Sorbet, is no longer available. It was a major factor for us to pick HomeTown Buffet on any given night.

Fried fish, which my wife always selected, is no longer regularly available. The last 4 of the last 5 times we came, on various nights, no fried fish.

The "fresh" tortillas are almost always hard as a rock, that is, they are inedible.

Now there are a variety of unappealing little pots that pretty much all look the same (mystery meat dishes?).

Chicken pot pies are a nice addition, if you also get a piece to chicken to cut up and add as a supplement to the mostly gravy under the pie crust.

The prices are up and the quality is down. Not the best way to attract and keep customers.</Text>< time>
1416853962808</time>

SAD TO SAY, BUT I am really DISAPPOINTED WITH HOMETOWN BUFFET NOW.  Use to be a place one could go and have a pretty decent meal of Quality and menu selection..

THE NEW MENU (as we see it) provides less VARIETY and QUALITY, and IS NOT TO OUR LIKING..........The new CEO has made changes, yes, but NOT FOR THE BETTER................to the point we WILL NO LONGER BE EATING THERE.  Went in for dinner Nov 29, 2014 and paid for two.

The first thing I preceded to do was to get some STEAK, WHAT? - NO STEAK!, YEP, NO STEAK and also tried TO GET A BAKED POTATO..........WELL GUESS WHAT....NO BAKED POTATO FOR DINNER, but was TOLD IT IS JUST SERVED ON THE LUNCH MENU.

........  THE BUFFET NO LONGER SERVES STEAK along with its ham and roast beef, etc..  WOULD YOU BELIEVE THAT IN PLACE OF STEAK, they NOW SERVE A PATHETIC TASTELESS HAMBURGER PATTY , yes I said HAMBURGER PATTY which NOW REPLACES STEAK ON THEIR DINNER MENU.  Thought they were finally getting their act together when they got rid of THEIR CHEAP LOW QUALITY GRISTLE STEAK   and replaced it with a higher quality steak without the gristle.

Heck, IF I WANT A HAMBURGER PATTY, I CAN GO TO MCDONALDS or IN AND OUT (just any drive in burger joint).

All the many little servings thingies they have in the little "skillet" type of containers, are non-edible...need to be done away with.

We had thought bout going to SIZZLER'S , NOW I BELIEVE THAT IS DEFINITELY THE CHOICE FOR DINNER FROM NOW ON.  GREATLY DISAPPOINTED WITH HOMETOWN BUFFET..........their new MENU needs to take a DUMP.  Come to think of it, it already has taken a DUMP.

In short, STAY AWAY.  AS FOR WE, THE PRICE GOES UP AND THE QUALITY OF THE NEW MENU SELECTION HAS  DIMINISHED GREATLY DOWNWARD.  AGAIN STAY AWAY.

........the new CEO HAS POISONED THE WELL..........

Think I will have to send an email to CEO or may just send him a snail mail of the above review.<//Text>
